<body>
Reports a common mistake in TypeScript code, when a class field is declared as a constructor parameter, and then this parameter is assigned.<br/>
In this case, the corresponding field <i>won't</i> be assigned, only the local parameter value is modified.
<pre><code>
class Foo {
  constructor(private p: number) {
    p = 1; //must be this.p = 1;
  }
}
</code></pre>
</body>
